commit.message:
Merge pull request #21 from idbrii/buffer-local

Allow settings to be buffer-local

Merge pull request #20 from idbrii/preferred-when-mixed

Add option for preferred values with tabs + spaces

Allow settings to be buffer-local

Only applies to indent settings (not max lines etc).

Add s:GetValue() to properly grab buffer-local options. Assumes if they
are active that we should use their value (instead of assuming existence
means 1) to allow us to force settings for specific filetypes.

To make most filetypes use 'expandtab', add this to vimrc:
    let g:detectindent_preferred_expandtab = 1
And for the exceptions that should use 'noexpandtab' add this to
after/ftplugin/FILETYPENAMEHERE.vim:
    let b:detectindent_preferred_expandtab = 1

Add documentation.

Add option for preferred values with tabs + spaces

Add detectindent_preferred_when_mixed so we use
detectindent_preferred_indent and detectindent_preferred_expandtab when
both tabs and spaces are found. This makes it easier for users to
enforce a "correct" setting when working in messy code.

Merge pull request #19 from tom95/vala-comments

Add vala to list of C style languages
add vala to list of C style languages
Add a README

Merge pull request #9 from jonasb/master

Made some minor improvements
Add the line number of the shortest leading spaces to the verbose output for debugging purposes
Skip comment lines since they are not dependable.
Add support for Java

Merge pull request #8 from blueyed/patch-1

Fix verbose_msg for no spaces/tabs.

Fix verbose_msg for no spaces/tabs.

Also, use "and" in general for these messages.

Merge pull request #7 from blueyed/command-with-bar

Add `-bar` to definition of `:DetectIndent`.

Add `-bar` to definition of `:DetectIndent`.

This will allow to use the bar (`|`) after the command, which comes in
handy in a custom mapping.

Improve verbosity.

  - Output internal states (`has_leading_tabs`, `has_leading_spaces`,
    `shortest_leading_spaces_run`, `longest_leading_spaces_run`).
  - Show differences from internal buffer values for &et, &sw, &ts and
    &sts.

Add "php" to rudimentary comment block detection.

This addresses issue #3
(https://github.com/ciaranm/detectindent/issues/closed#issue/3).

Be more verbose.

This adds a new setting g:detectindent_verbosity (default: 1) and lets
the plugin be more chatty if &verbose is >= this setting.
also ignore c-style comments found in javascript which will throw off indentation

Limit number of lines that are analysed to improve oepning speed if file is very large.

Default number of lines to analyse is 1024. Default can be changed with g:detectindent_max_lines_to_analyse variable.

Signed-off-by: Pauli Nieminen <suokkos@gmail.com>
Only modify the buffer-local option values.
Set 'sw' & 'ts'/'sw' & 'sts' consistently based on 'et'
Allow users to prevent the plugin from being loaded.
Correct variable name: tabsize => indent

Ignore whitespace only lines.

Paying attention solely to lines with actual content should improve the
heuristics as those lines are more likely to be paid due attention.  Lines of
pure whitespace probably go unnoticed by most people and are therefore less
likely to follow the proper indent style.

Correct line index bug in “skip comments” loop.

Since the loop was retrieving the next line to examine before advancing the
line index, the index ended up being two lines past the end of the comment
instead of the expected one line.
